description.27: Namor vs. The Living Rock...plus Aunt Serr's monstrous victims put up quite a fight!
description.36: Namor's quest for his missing father continues here!
description.41: Spider-Man gives Namor an assist against Turalla the Mad mutant!
description.45: Namor earns the ire of the United States military after squatting in an abandoned prison!
description.52: Namor swears off Atlantis forever after mourning the loss of his beloved Lady Dorma!
description.57: Lady Dorma may lose her claim as Atlantis' queen after last issue's switcheroo by Llyra!
description.70: The animals flee in terror of the Devil Bird! But when Lorna discovers that this "Bird" is actually a disguised helicopter, more questions than answers are raised!
description.71: More 1950s adventures of Captain America, Bucky and the Human Torch!
description.72: Sound the wedding bells! Namor finally puts a ring on Lady Dorma!
description.77: Given the ability to steal items and people from the television set, a man will soon take something that he will deeply regret!
description.79: The Avengers are called in to quell the rampage of the Titans Three!
description.81: While Cap and Bucky continue their crusade against enemy spies, the Torch and Toro have an extraterrestrial encounter!
description.82: After a Toro/Torch team-up, Captain America and Bucky must extract themselves from captivity...or end up prisoners of war!
description.83: No matter the temptation, don't look in the box. This issue is not for the faint of heart!
description.84: A "ghost" is haunting the jungles! Lorna investigates before more of her tribespeople are terrorized!
description.86: The Torch and Toro investigate a group of spies!
description.88: After being convicted for murder, a man reveals himself to be something more than supernatural!
description.89: Are you familiar with the Salem Witch Trials? This issue follows a similar path, instead this time the witches may actually exist...
description.90: Guest-starring the Hulk and Silver Surfer! It's a team-up for the ages when Namor is joined by these two titans to take down a diabolical general!
description.91: A lunar rocket-testing site falls under attack by enemy spies! Thankfully, Toro and Torch are there to save the day!
description.95: Cap takes the fight to the communist saboteurs that have infiltrated the United States! Plus, a special tale featuring Jim Hammond, the Human Torch!
description.96: Though we all get lonely sometimes, maybe getting in a coffin right next to the dead isn't the best idea...
description.97: Greg Knight has been subdued by the venomous snake Fang! M'Tuba and Lorna may be Greg's only chance of survival against this serpentine evil!

0.text: A man who despises his own species may wish for it all back when he loses the ability to see them...

2.text: Who wouldn’t want to possess a ring that can make your wildest dreams come true?!

3.text: A couple on holiday encounter colonial hero Paul Revere…in his own time!

6.text: A scientist creates a pill that could change the world forever, but a dream convinces him not to pursue his goal.

7.text: Only those seeking TRUE adventure would dare to venture into the Land of Vanishing Men!

8.text: The Black Knight takes on the Dragon of Kentswood Swamp!

9.text: Six people plunge into a body of water. Seven people come up.

10.text: Six mysterious tales that will bring up more questions than they will solve!

13.text: A ship's captain is revealed to be Neptune's son!

14.text: A bitter man invents a machine to transform his wife into whatever he so pleases. We'll see if karma comes back to bite him…

15.text: A teleportation machine may prove an excellent advancement to mankind, but it can also be used to efficiently commit crime.

16.text: Some people will do just about anything for an inheritance…

19.text: A group of killers attack an innocent family! But a family member from the victims’ pasts may have something to say about it…

20.text: Utterly captivated by a mermaid, a man undergoes an operation to live with his love in the great seas. What could possibly go wrong?

22.text: Barely alive and washed onto a beach, a man finds he is much larger than anyone else he encounters.

23.text: After a man finds out his friends don't believe in mermaids, he finds himself an opportunity to catch a fake one! It was a ruse, an elaborate prank! Or was it…?

24.text: The Black Knight assists King Arthur in his toppling of Sir Guy Wandrell.

28.text: A painter, who has been dead for two hundred years, returns to life for one final masterpiece.

29.text: The original Puppet Master! A man who creates figures of himself meets a bizarre fate.

32.text: These stories have one major recurring theme: otherworldly beings’ boredom with humanity.

33.text: Don't be too greedy or you could end up like The Man in the Sky…

34.text: Mordred devises a plot to fell the Black Knight! Merlin the Magician uses every trick up his sleeve.

35.text: Ghosts of man's best friend lead the stranded to safety!

37.text: When Lady Rosamund is kidnapped by Lief the Lucky, Sir Percy alone must rescue the damsel!

38.text: After being captured by a U.F.O., a man has his entire memory wiped.

40.text: In this issue? Meet a scientist who has the power to turn off the sun!

42.text: The haunted drawer! A married couple must not have heard that curiosity killed the cat...

43.text: The Arthurian legend of the Black Knight begins!

46.text: The First Comics Code Authority approved issue, featuring a mysterious story about a prisoner in a bottle…

47.text: A Martian has a craving to steal Earth's mightiest landmarks!

50.text: A confident man bets he can stay one entire night at a haunted house. But he loses that bet by turning into a ghost himself!

51.text: Not everything is made of flesh and blood…What happens when the things we create soon become out of our control?

54.text: Two bodiless gaseous forms have their wishes granted when they transform into humans!

58.text: Extraterrestrials have the brilliant idea of displacing humans from Earth. Is this truly the Apocalypse?

59.text: Step Lively, Please. The Strangest of Tales resumes.

61.text: Marvelman enters the sleepy realm of Nod! But all is not as it seems in this fairytale kingdom…

62.text: Miniature figures magically come alive to attack the person who discovered them!

63.text: Dr. Gargunza spins yet another plot against Moran! And this one is really heating up!

66.text: The soul of an ideal lover is trapped inside a figurine.

67.text: A man becomes one with a tree…a bit too literally!

68.text: You're not seeing double! That's another Marvelman on the cover! But just who is the doppelganger that bears an uncanny resemblance to Moran?

73.text: Kimota! Will Moran be able to divert a bomb that's threatening the lives of hundreds? Perhaps his super alter ego Marvelman can!

78.text: Toy blocks are well and good, unless they're the ones featured in this issue which destroy actual buildings once scattered.

80.text: Micky Moran gets a chilly reception from the Abominable Snowman!

86.text: The Torch and Toro investigate a group of spies!

87.text: Marvelman enters a sci-fi nightmare when he goes up against a living computer!

92.text: Marvelman Vs. Sabotage -- don't miss out!

93.text: An unfinished robot weeks away from completion suddenly acts on its own whim! The problem? This robot has an affinity for murder! Will its scientist pull the plug before his creation embarks on a killing spree?

94.text: A classic adventure starring the Original Human Torch!

98.text: Enter…the nefarious Dr. Gargunza! Devoid of any conscience, Marvelman finds a terrifying new foe in the doctor.
